heaviest_rainfall.status: The most intense rainfall recorded took place on 04 January 2025, with precipitation totalling 36.8mm.  The rain fell at 4.6mm per hour at times over the course of the 37.2 hour storm.

heaviest_rainrate.status: Today ranked 10th for the heaviest rainfall ever in our records, with a peak intensity of 10.1mm per hour sustained for 16.6 hours, resulting in a total accumulation of 9.37mm.  27.0mm per hour is the maximum rain rate ever recorded on 02 September 2025, during a 15.0 hour storm which dumped 21.19mm of rain from the clouds.

longest_rain.status: Today's rainstorm ranked 10th on our record table for the length of the storm as it lasted 16.6 hours; it delivered 9.37mm of rain at a maximum rate of 10.1mm per hour.  The longest rain storm on record lasted 37.2 hours on 04 January 2025 when 36.8mm of rain fell and at one point was falling at 4.6mm per hour.
